Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.86,0:01:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was to be wed, I passed \Nthrough the forest to the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.05,0:01:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I think... it was probably then that\N it had attached itself to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.57,0:01:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Without my noticing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a small green stain upon my head wear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.17,0:02:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't until after the ceremony that I noticed it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.07,0:02:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was quite ominous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.35,0:02:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The following year,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.19,0:02:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I bore my first child...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.13,0:02:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is him, our eldest son, Watahiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.65,0:02:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Since these spots appeared,\Nhe has continued to grow weaker...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.97,0:02:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and whenever I see them, I remember that stain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.09,0:02:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,lf... I am mistaken, please forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.30,0:02:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did this child have a human shape when he was born?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.41,0:02:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.97,0:02:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He was not even a beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.27,0:02:54.27,EP Title BG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,0)\p1\blur1}m 0 0 l 950 0 950 100 0 100
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.27,0:02:54.27,EP Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,0)\be1}Cotton Changeling
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.19,0:02:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even three months had passed...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.98,0:03:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought I would be \Ninvited back to that house again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.20,0:03:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.04,0:03:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.37,0:03:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I read your letter. Is there still time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.46,0:03:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... Let's hurry, to the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.86,0:03:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.27,0:03:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to... do as you told us but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.76,0:03:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's fine. Thanks for letting me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.21,0:03:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But, to be honest, I never thought\Nit would come to this so soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.78,0:03:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.27,0:03:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He has been growing disturbingly quickly lately!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Did this child have a human shape when he was born?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.49,0:03:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Aki... are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.74,0:03:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll explain the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.97,0:03:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was not even a beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.20,0:04:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't even give a cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.60,0:04:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a strange green mass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.54,0:04:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Aki!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.93,0:04:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.32,0:04:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.74,0:04:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we knew it, it had slipped\Nbelow the house... and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.81,0:04:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife desperately wanted a child but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.01,0:04:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking it to be impossible now, \N she spent her days shut inside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.18,0:04:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... a year later...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.33,0:04:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.33,0:04:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it coming from beneath the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if someone abandoned him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.13,0:05:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He is that child... our child.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.09,0:05:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He does look a lot like Aki...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.79,0:05:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He's grown to be a human since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.79,0:05:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid deep down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.91,0:05:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But I decided to believe that it was so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.93,0:05:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That child... Watahiko grew fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.11,0:05:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He liked to eat fresh small fish and fruits from trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.25,0:05:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and in a little over half a year, he grew to be the size of a three-year-old child.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.28,0:05:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However... his mind was that of an infant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't show any feelings or utter any words.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite that, with his face \Nincreasingly resembling our own,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.67,0:06:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I, too, became attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.34,0:06:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, one night...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.45,0:06:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A cat? How noisy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.60,0:06:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoo... shoo...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.69,0:06:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet another child was under our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.19,0:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, he looks like Watahiko in every way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We should raise him in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.70,0:06:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we'll have more.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.20,0:06:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say scary things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That premonition was proved correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.62,0:06:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Watahiko continued to multiply,\Nsprouting up every half a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times I dug up\Nthe ground beneath the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never find anything strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:07:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... from the beginning of this year, \Nour eldest son's health began to deteriorate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.97,0:07:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He would sleep most of the day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.19,0:07:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and his green eruptions would increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.22,0:07:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctors threw in the towel...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.77,0:07:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I heard about people like yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.26,0:07:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.28,0:07:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,even we, mushi-shi, have no way to save this child.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.14,0:07:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He's reached the end of his lifespan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.17,0:07:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a mushi called {\i1}Watahaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a green form that looks like \Ncotton and floats in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.73,0:07:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It enters the body of a pregnant woman\Nand becomes parasitic upon the ovum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.04,0:07:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's born, it's in the form of slime,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.51,0:07:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and quickly escapes below the floors or into the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,After a year, it sends a {\i1}hitotake{\i0} in the shape of a baby to its parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That and the rate of his multiplying\Nexactly match the records of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.08,0:07:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,However, just to be sure, would it be all right to take a look beneath your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.40,0:08:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No thanks, I don't need any lighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.15,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's here, and it's grown quite large.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.34,0:08:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake. It's a {\i1}Watahaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.32,0:08:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.49,0:08:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.62,0:08:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a good look at this soil in the sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.83,0:08:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}hitotake{\i0} are connected to the main body of this mushi by thread-like things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.58,0:08:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're nothing more than a part of the mushi to send the main body nourishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.51,0:08:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It cant' be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.37,0:08:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That child will soon end his purpose, and will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.93,0:08:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment he dies, he will cough up a lot of seeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.75,0:08:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that happens, we must kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.97,0:08:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.46,0:08:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think we called you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.14,0:09:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That child... please save him from\Nthat mushi or whatever it's called.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.61,0:09:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no longer any "child" I can save.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.66,0:09:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Those "children" are mushi \Nwearing the skin of your child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And they are the very ones who killed your child who was supposed to be born.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.34,0:09:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Please... understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.27,0:09:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.46,0:09:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's... all right to hate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.78,0:09:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for persuading your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.22,0:09:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She still won't talk to me, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.27,0:09:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We raised him for more than three years...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.98,0:09:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.09,0:10:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But she wants to keep the other \Nchildren with us at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.20,0:10:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm begging you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.38,0:10:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave them alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.21,0:10:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Until they show symptoms, they're of no harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.02,0:10:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In exchange... I'll be sure to kill the second eldest
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.14,0:10:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next born before they cough up seeds...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.57,0:10:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The lifespan of a {\i1}Watahaki{\i0} spans \Nanywhere from ten to thirty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.13,0:10:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot tell how many more years it will continue
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or how many more "children" you'll have to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.18,0:10:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.87,0:10:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... I promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.39,0:10:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You told me that you were afraid of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.58,0:10:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet you're saying you wish to raise them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.54,0:10:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't want to make my wife sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:11:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Aki calls the remaining four Watahiko and adores them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.47,0:11:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If we lose all of them, I don't know what will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.71,0:11:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Long ago, she married into the family of a prominent merchant from a town beyond the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.19,0:11:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There, she gave birth to the awaited heir,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.65,0:11:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but before he was even a year old, \Nit seems he died of something trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.25,0:11:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That was why they got divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.46,0:11:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, why must these cruel things happen to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.38,0:11:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Until now, it seems that "{\i1}Watahaki{\i0} children"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.98,0:11:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,were all immediately killed as soon as it was understood what they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.23,0:11:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, they let the roots run dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.15,0:11:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no record of letting its offspring live,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.62,0:11:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,since they will become dangerous later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.59,0:11:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot say for sure that they will not pose a threat in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.85,0:11:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.91,0:12:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then again...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.22,0:12:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they may not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.78,0:12:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Exterminating the ones I'm not sure \Nof is brash and I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I have reasons I can't continue to keep watch here,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.60,0:12:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but I will return in three months to see how things are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything happens, send me a letter to that address.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.39,0:12:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm indebted to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.78,0:12:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter arrived before even three months had passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.66,0:12:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There... He came. It's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.52,0:12:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.86,0:12:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.75,0:12:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.18,0:12:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Watahiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.02,0:12:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.09,0:12:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.86,0:13:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems my wife has consented.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We're raising something unnatural.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.31,0:13:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We must at least follow our agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.49,0:13:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Aki, Ginko has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.69,0:13:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.16,0:13:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.05,0:13:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.26,0:13:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.95,0:13:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.03,0:13:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You are awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.83,0:13:48.09,Alt,,0,0,0,,Owowowowow...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.09,0:13:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You should stay in bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.35,0:13:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Darn... I want to go home...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.27,0:13:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I really have no way to make up for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.98,0:14:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep her in the sleeping room until everything is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.41,0:14:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... please do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.24,0:14:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought... she'd understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.35,0:14:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that the situation has changed quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.91,0:14:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.83,0:14:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to tell you sooner,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.41,0:14:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But those children...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.04,0:14:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not only that their growth has speeded up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.20,0:14:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, my fourth son was peeling a chestnut,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.71,0:14:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something I taught only to my second son.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Although my second son finally\Nlearned it after much effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,my fourth son might have learned it by watching...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.22,0:14:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed that they were gradually getting smarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.10,0:14:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My, you've gotten soaked by the rain haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.37,0:14:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get you a change of clothes, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.58,0:14:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.25,0:14:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.58,0:14:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy... I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.83,0:15:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Aki... He... He talked!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.61,0:15:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.38,0:15:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get you something right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.23,0:15:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then our second son began to show those symptoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.95,0:15:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still too early...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.11,0:15:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just recently that this happened to our eldest...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.05,0:15:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.71,0:15:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This... is our duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.22,0:15:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, I'm afraid of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't kill me... Save me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.75,0:15:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I still want to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.75,0:15:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already become like a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.68,0:15:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though they're responsible for our child's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.71,0:15:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we can no longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.47,0:15:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How can this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.77,0:15:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's now gained the ability to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.34,0:15:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, it's always had this function.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.29,0:16:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Could it be that it sensed danger\Nbecause of the eldest son's death?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.22,0:16:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not only that, but the information gained by one is circulated among all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.95,0:16:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Each one is part of the main body and connected to the others at the base.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They all receive information for five people at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.87,0:16:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They learn quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.26,0:16:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But... they're ''human-like things''?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.73,0:16:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.21,0:16:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What lives within them... is a fungus that thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.95,0:16:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We've failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to be killed. We're going to be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.63,0:16:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to protect the seeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.20,0:16:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there was a way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We've forgotten. We've forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.09,0:16:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When we learned how to speak, we lost our memory of...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.85,0:17:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,3400)}how to... how to protect our seeds...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.85,0:17:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... well, I can somehow get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.87,0:17:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.81,0:17:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your second son is in the back room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.54,0:17:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.82,0:17:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.84,0:17:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, I'm going to remove the roots and take the remaining children with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.03,0:17:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I can no longer leave them with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.42,0:17:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Save me, don't kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.98,0:17:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.93,0:18:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must you kill us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you eat human children.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.14,0:18:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not our fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.79,0:18:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not our fault either...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.00,0:18:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.25,0:18:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you are going to die without leaving seeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.98,0:18:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.68,0:18:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.31,0:18:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.22,0:18:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.76,0:18:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they trying to burn the house along with the roots under the house?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.15,0:18:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it, could it be that you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.86,0:18:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was written in the scrolls that you brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.22,0:18:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, we'd be able to do this unconsciously.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.51,0:19:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the only way to protect our seeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.82,0:19:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We win.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.78,0:19:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.75,0:19:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't come this way. Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.75,0:19:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Watahiko! Where are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.64,0:19:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the ones who set the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.81,0:19:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll do anything for their seeds!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of mushi they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.59,0:19:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They're already my children!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.57,0:19:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Aki!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.29,0:19:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Watahiko... Watahiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:19:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Watahiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.05,0:19:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Watahiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.95,0:20:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The roots have completely disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.01,0:20:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When a {\i1}Watahaki{\i0} plunges into\N a crisis, such as disasters,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.59,0:20:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it cuts its {\i1}hitotake{\i0} off from its roots and tries to at least let the seeds escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.27,0:20:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}hitotake{\i0} change their form \Nand go into a long hibernation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.57,0:20:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this... it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.75,0:20:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know when they'll be reborn...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.35,0:20:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be after you both pass away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.21,0:20:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the case, until that time comes, I'll leave it with both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.64,0:20:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.94,0:21:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll always carry it with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.69,0:21:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you give them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.72,0:21:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A mineral.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.33,0:21:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was part of my livelihood's provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.06,0:21:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A complete loss...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.70,0:21:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.99,0:21:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure are a mysterious creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.90,0:21:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Look who's talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.77,0:21:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Weren't you supposed to hibernate?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.34,0:21:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what all the records said you would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.56,0:21:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care, I'm not tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.45,0:21:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.85,0:21:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren't you killing me now\N while you have the chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.35,0:21:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the end of your life hasn't come yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.38,0:21:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What a mysterious creature you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.31,0:21:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough. Go to sleep already.
